The ATO, set up in 1976, comprises Angola, Tanzania, Liberia, The Central African Republic, Cameroon, Nigeria, Zaire, the Congo, Corte D'Ivoire, Gabon, Sao Tome and Principe, Ghana, Equatorial Guinea.
